<paragraph blockId="17.[151,1437,1311,1578]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">
This was a rare species; the only specimen found had narrow buccal and pharyngeal tubes with no drop between them. Three rod-shaped macroplacoids but no microplacoid was within the pharyngeal bulb. Body length of the only specimen found was 
<number box="[627,671,1432,1458]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" value="528.0">528</number>
μm, and it was in a LF sample (Table 
<number box="[1142,1158,1432,1458]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" value="3.0">3</number>
). The species has been cited in Europe, Asia, 
<collectingCountry box="[433,534,1472,1498]" name="United States of America" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">America</collectingCountry>
and Oceania. In the Iberian Peninsula, it has been recorded for 
<collectingCountry box="[1338,1436,1472,1498]" name="Andorra" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Andorra</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Maucci" box="[159,516,1512,1538]" pageId="17" pageNumber="29" refString="Maucci, W. &amp; Durante Pasa, V. (1984) Macrobiotus lusitanicus sp. nov. nuova specie di eutardigrado del portogallo nord - occidentale. Bollettino del Museo Civico di Storia Naturale di Verona, 11, 319 - 326." type="journal article" year="1984">
Maucci &amp; Durante Pasa 
<number box="[456,516,1512,1538]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" value="1984.0">1984</number>
</bibRefCitation>
) and 
<collectingCountry box="[586,686,1512,1538]" name="Portugal" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Portugal</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Maucci" box="[702,1063,1512,1538]" pageId="17" pageNumber="29" refString="Maucci, W. &amp; Durante Pasa, V. (1985) I Tardigradi della fauna Portoghese. Anais da Facultade de Ciencias, Universidade do Porto, 65 (1 / 4), 127 - 174." type="journal article" year="1985">
Maucci &amp; Durante Pasa 
<number box="[1000,1063,1512,1538]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" value="1985.0">1985</number>
</bibRefCitation>
). It is the first record for 
<collectingCountry box="[1370,1437,1512,1538]" name="Spain" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Spain</collectingCountry>
(
<tableCitation box="[158,250,1552,1578]" captionStart="TABLE 2" captionStartId="4.[151,239,1706,1730]" captionTargetBox="[159,1400,1802,1996]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="TABLE 2. Tardigrada species found in the Sierra de Guadarrama. New records (NR) for Europe (Eur), the Iberian Peninsula (IbPn), Spain (Spn) and Madrid Province (Mad) are indicated." httpUri="http://table.plazi.org/id/DF5C665F3D5AFF91FF689BECFC06F97C" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" tableUuid="DF5C665F3D5AFF91FF689BECFC06F97C">
Table 
<number box="[233,250,1552,1578]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" value="2.0">2</number>
